ENTRY.Author: Maxime Gouzevitch
ENTRY.TEXT:
The RE11 chamber position was measured today:

 

Laser x = 3198 mm from Jura wall

Laser z = 3137 mm from Upstream wall

 

Beam x = +80 cm from laser position

Chamber z = + 30 cm from laser position

 

Using the Flucka from attached PDF:

 

Point U2 is: z = -2.9 and rate is 7.2e6 gamma/s/cm2

Point U3 is: z = -4.9 and rate is 3.5e6 gamma/s/cm2

Our chamber z = -6+3.137+0.3 = -2.56 m

I parametrise locally the rate by:

R(z)  = a*z+b

with a = 1.85e6 gamma/s/cm2 / m       and       b = 1.26 e7 gamma/s/cm2

So we obtain at the chamber position: R(chamber) = 7.9e6 gamma/s/cm2
